The paper proposes a new model for enhancing the expression ability of traditional RBMs for image clustering tasks. The paper discusses the learning procedure and the proposed model's performance in comparison to traditional RBMs and semi-supervised clustering algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the paper proposes a new model for enhancing the expression ability of traditional RBMs, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, since the paper uses image datasets for evaluation, cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible sub-category.
